This paper focuses on the lifecycle of OSS contributors and their transitions in and out of contributing, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The study also examines the health of OSS communities, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI) or cybernetics (cs.CY). The analysis of reasons for transitions could also be relevant to software development (cs.SD) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
